  "title": "Assistant Manager Business Development and marketing",
  "description": "<p><strong>HENRI\nCOLLINS INTERNATIONAL (SINGAPORE) PTE. LTD </strong></p><p><strong>Position: Assistant Marketing cum\nBusiness Development Manager.</strong></p><p><strong>Job Scope: </strong></p><p>·      \nGrowing the company's market presence and share</p><p>·       Generating\nnew business opportunities and creating a strong brand identity.</p><p><strong>Marketing\naspect</strong>:</p><p>·       Responsible for developing and\nexecuting marketing plans and strategies, \n</p><p>·       Customer engagement and sales, to achieve\nbusiness goals and targets.:</p><p>·           \nConduct market research to understand\nindustry trends, customer behaviours, competitor strategies, and market\nopportunities.</p><p>·           \nAnalyse customer needs and preferences\nto tailor marketing strategies to achieve sales revenue </p><p>·           \nEstablish and foster good customer relationships.</p><p><strong>Business\ndevelopment aspect</strong>:</p><p>·      \nIncrease\nour presence in Indonesia, Thailand, Taiwan, USA, UAE, Saudi Arabia, Oman,\nRussia</p><p>·           \nPromote\nour products ie berets (military and fashion), Big caps, Sunhats, Work Suits,\nJerseys, Singlets, Shirts and pants, etc. to above countries via physical\npresence, e-commerce, digital marketing, etc. </p><p>·           \nVenture\nand promote our products in the Military and Defence and Security industry,\nFashion, F&B, Airlines, Hospitality, Healthcare, retailers, shopping malls,\netc<strong>.</strong></p><p>·           \nDevelop\nstrategies and plans for lead generation and sales</p><p>·           \nPrepare proposals, bids and\npresentations for new business opportunities.</p><p>·           \nHelp to negotiate contracts and terms\nwith clients and partners.</p><p>·           \nMonitor industry trends with a view to\nkeeping up to date with industry developments, market conditions, and\ncompetitor activities to identify business opportunities for existing and new\nproducts.</p><p>·           \nTracking sales data to ensure targets\nare achieved </p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Marketing or equivalent with at least 3 years of marketing\n     experience.</li><li>Strong communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills.</li><li>Self-motivated, results-oriented and resourceful with ability to\n     work independently.</li><li>Ability to create and execute strategic marketing plans and\n     initiatives.</li><li>Analytical skills to assess market data, evaluate business\n     performance and identify new business opportunities for existing products\n     and new products.</li></ul>",
